Date:   Tue Apr 14 22:41:49 2026 +0300

    [wsi] Don't treat SDL_SetWindowPosition failure as fatal

    On Wayland, SDL_SetWindowPosition fails because the protocol does not
    allow positioning non-popup windows. This caused enterFullscreenMode to
    abort before reaching SDL_SetWindowFullscreen, breaking fullscreen for
    all SDL3 WSI games on Wayland.

    SDL internally stores the pending display ID before the backend rejects
    the move, so the call still serves its purpose as a display selection
    hint. Downgrade the error to a warning and continue to fullscreen.
